# Mei — top-level env hint.
#
# Most workspace packages read env from their own `.env` file. To configure
# them all, copy each per-service example to a real `.env` next to it:
#
#   cp apps/mobile/.env.example          apps/mobile/.env
#   cp services/api/.env.example         services/api/.env
#   cp services/stylist/.env.example     services/stylist/.env
#   cp services/mock-server/.env.example services/mock-server/.env   # optional
#
# Then fill in the values. Per-service env files are gitignored.
#
# Production / staging secrets live in their respective dashboards
# (Supabase, Render, GitHub Actions) — never commit a filled-in copy.
# See `docs/CREDENTIALS.md` for the full map of where each secret lives.
#
# This file itself doesn't drive any service. It exists to point you at
# the per-service examples and at the credentials doc.
